description:
&lt;p&gt;A new and exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Midwife to lead on the key deliverables associated with Public Health within Maternity Services at The Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals. As an experienced Midwife with a broad range of clinical experience, you will be pivotal in ensuring that women and their families receive bespoke packages of care which meet their individual needs and maximise good outcomes. This post is offered on a fixed term or as a secondment opportunity for a period of 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic Midwife who will form part of the Senior Midwifery Team and work closely with members of the wider multi-professional team both within the Acute Hospital and Community. It is essential that you have a good working knowledge of the Public Health agenda and an understanding of how this relates to local, regional and national initiatives. Work will align to a range of prevention initiatives undertaken through the NTWD Local Maternity System (LMS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Areas of specific focus will be in promoting smoke free pregnancies and reducing tobacco dependency; perinatal mental health; increasing rates of vaccination and immunisation; advising on and supporting healthy weight in pregnancy. You will work closely with the Maternity Matrons and members of the Specialist Midwifery Team, particularly our Infant Feeding Co-ordinator and Drug and Alcohol Midwives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent leadership skills are essential for this role, as it the ability to use enhanced levels of interpersonal and communication skill, in order to network with multi-agency providers of health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting the Directorate Senior Leadership Team, you will be responsible for planning, implementing and monitoring all actions within the agreed work-plan, reporting on compliance and key performance indicators. A good understanding of The Maternity Transformation Programme and Better Births will be beneficial in ensuring that all key deliverables align with the priority in ensuring better outcomes for mothers, babies and families in our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel that you have the key qualities for this important role, and the passion and drive to support in improving and developing our Maternity Services, we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Watson, Matron for Postnatal and Community Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle.watson12@nhs.net Tel 0191 28 25768&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
